Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1

Thanks Brian.

Pretty neat use of the swift client's inbuilt retry mechanism.

Couple of paperwork bits (sorry).

Can you add DocImpact to the commit message, and update the relevant .rst files? (Eg see https://review.openstack.org/#/c/48913/). In particular users should be told what to set swift_store_reader_class to if they want the upload retry behaviour. I think a documented warning for end users about potential memory starvation would be helpful also.

An equivalent functional test to 48913 would be nice if possible (I could help if you hit a couple of gotchas), but I know some of those swift functional tests are a bit stale.

Thanks.

Patch Set 4:

@Stuart - Sure, I'd be happy to do that.  I will also take a whack at resuscitating the swift functional tests and see how that goes.

(1 comment)

Overall looks good. Just had a couple of questions:-

1. Haven't checked the swiftclient to ensure if we log the requests when we hit the seek and tell of the BufferedReader. What do you think about adding those here to indicate that they've been hit, if not already so?

2. What do you think about logging the buffer size and(or) buffer size of each req., whenever something is being buffered and being removed from memory to debug any possible memory leaks?
